# Task 4 – Linux Firewall Setup (UFW)

## What I Did
This task required configuring a firewall on Linux using UFW to:
- Set the default policy to **deny incoming** and **allow outgoing** traffic.
- Allow SSH (port 22) to prevent remote lockout.
- Block Telnet (port 23).
- Enable the firewall and verify that port 23 is blocked.

## Steps
1. Installed UFW and backed up current firewall rules.
2. Set default deny/allow policies.
3. Allowed SSH traffic.
4. Blocked Telnet (port 23).
5. Enabled the firewall.
6. Saved firewall status to `ufw-status.txt`.
7. Verified blocking with `nmap` scan.

## Evidence
- **ufw-status.txt** – shows active rules.
- **outputs.txt** – terminal output from commands.
- **screenshots/** – GUI or terminal screenshots of the firewall and tests.

## Verification
- SSH allowed 
- Telnet blocked 
- Firewall enabled and running 

## How to Reproduce
Run commands from `commands.txt` on any Debian/Ubuntu/Kali Linux system.



# Install UFW
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ufw -y

# Backup current rules
sudo iptables-save > ~/iptables-before.rules
sudo cp /etc/ufw/user.rules ~/user.rules.before 2>/dev/null

# Set defaults
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing
Default incoming policy changed to 'deny'
(be sure to update your rules accordingly)
Default outgoing policy changed to 'allow'
(be sure to update your rules accordingly)



# Allow SSH
sudo ufw allow 22/tcp

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ sudo ufw allow 22/tcp
Rules updated
Rules updated (v6)



# Block Telnet
sudo ufw deny 23/tcp

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ sudo ufw deny 23/tcp
Rules updated
Rules updated (v6)



# Enable firewall
sudo ufw enable

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ sudo ufw enable
Firewall is active and enabled on system startup


# Save status
sudo ufw status verbose > ~/ufw-status.txt

# Install nmap
sudo apt install nmap -y


# Test port 23
nmap -p 23 127.0.0.1

┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ nmap -p 23 127.0.0.1

Starting Nmap 7.95 ( https://nmap.org ) at 2025-08-10 09:45 EDT
Nmap scan report for localhost (127.0.0.1)
Host is up (0.00020s latency).
PORT   STATE  SERVICE
23/tcp closed telnet
Nmap done: 1 IP address (1 host up) scanned in 0.09 seconds


